Hmm.

02:20.567 --> 02:21.834
Finally.

02:21.834 --> 02:24.200
Come in.

02:24.200 --> 02:25.467
A disgrace.

02:29.234 --> 02:31.133
Where are the towels?

02:31.133 --> 02:33.100
I don't see any towels.

02:33.100 --> 02:36.968
Wh-what is that
behind your back?

02:41.734 --> 02:42.734
What-- Hey!

02:42.734 --> 02:45.567
Aah!

03:27.801 --> 03:29.467
Okay, it's vacation time.

03:29.467 --> 03:32.934
Peg, kids, we're going
to Poppy's by the Tree

03:32.934 --> 03:37.167
in picturesque
Dumpwater, Florida.

03:39.234 --> 03:41.834
Show some excitement!

03:41.834 --> 03:43.801
Well, I guess
it's up to me.

03:43.801 --> 03:44.834
Dad?
Yes, Bud?

03:44.834 --> 03:46.868
I thought we all
voted on Hawaii?

03:46.868 --> 03:49.467
That was just a vote, Bud.
Didn't mean anything.

03:50.834 --> 03:53.033
Al, honey,
you promised this year

03:53.033 --> 03:55.000
we could take
a real vacation.

03:55.000 --> 03:57.434
You know, someplace we don't
look out our windows

03:57.434 --> 04:00.634
and see chain
gangs working.

04:00.634 --> 04:01.901
Come on, Peg.

04:01.901 --> 04:05.634
We still sing those songs
we learned down there.

04:05.634 --> 04:07.667
But this year I found
something really special.

04:07.667 --> 04:09.868
Look at this brochure, Peg.

04:09.868 --> 04:12.734
This place has
everything Hawaii has.

04:12.734 --> 04:15.534
It's got sunshine,
a palm tree...

04:15.534 --> 04:18.100
uh, quicksand.

04:18.100 --> 04:22.033
But the best part is,
it's in the United States.

04:22.033 --> 04:25.601
So are the sewers
of Manhattan, Dad.

04:25.601 --> 04:28.801
Or am I spoiling
next year's vacation?

04:28.801 --> 04:32.200
Al, we all appreciate your
efforts at finding

04:32.200 --> 04:36.400
the cheapest places in America,
but Dumpwater, Florida, Al?

04:36.400 --> 04:38.501
You're gonna judge a place
by its name?

04:38.501 --> 04:40.300
If we did that, we never
would have experienced

04:40.300 --> 04:43.367
Six Toe,
Arkansas.

04:43.367 --> 04:44.601
Remember that soup,
kids?

04:44.601 --> 04:47.868
And don't forget those
underground fires.

04:47.868 --> 04:50.367
Dumpwater's gonna make
Six Toe look sick.

04:50.367 --> 04:53.601
And the best part is,
it's only $8 a night.

04:53.601 --> 04:55.601
See that'll give us plenty
of extra money to...

04:55.601 --> 04:57.267
Well, let's see...

04:57.267 --> 05:01.434
I don't know, but it'll
leave us plenty of money.

05:02.934 --> 05:04.501
My decision is made.

05:04.501 --> 05:07.834
Now, if people don't want
to go to Poppy's,

05:07.834 --> 05:09.901
we can use that money
to buy one of those

05:09.901 --> 05:12.734
soft toilet seats,
and make every day a vacation.

05:14.434 --> 05:15.868
Poppy's.
Poppy's.

05:15.868 --> 05:18.234
Well, kids,
it is near a nice tree.

05:18.234 --> 05:19.534
You betcha, Peg.

05:19.534 --> 05:21.534
And the best part is--

05:21.534 --> 05:25.834
We're taking the family car.

05:25.834 --> 05:27.434
You betcha.

05:27.434 --> 05:30.434
And that way, we get
to see all the sights.

05:30.434 --> 05:32.400
You mean like the house
that defies gravity?

05:32.400 --> 05:33.634
That's our first stop.

05:33.634 --> 05:36.067
That was supposed to be
a surprise for the kids.

05:36.067 --> 05:37.334
You didn't hear that, kids.

05:37.334 --> 05:39.434
Uh, yeah, we did, Dad.

05:39.434 --> 05:41.267
Actually, Dad,

05:41.267 --> 05:44.167
can we listen to the oldies
station all the way down?

05:44.167 --> 05:46.367
Please?
We can.

05:46.367 --> 05:49.167
Do we get to stop at Howard
Johnson's for Pez?

05:49.167 --> 05:50.868
We do.

05:50.868 --> 05:52.801
And all the way
through speed-trap country,

05:52.801 --> 05:55.067
do I get to pretend
I'm in labor?

05:55.067 --> 05:56.267
You do.

05:56.267 --> 05:58.267
Now, kids, I want you
to go upstairs,

05:58.267 --> 06:00.167
lay out all the clothes
you want to take,

06:00.167 --> 06:02.067
and keep this in mind--

06:02.067 --> 06:06.300
the first Howard Johnson's,
the Pez is on dad.

06:06.300 --> 06:08.133
[DOORBELL RINGS]

06:08.133 --> 06:10.868
That must be
Robin Leach.

06:13.767 --> 06:16.901
Can I get some
help here?

06:18.467 --> 06:21.067
Well, here it is.

06:21.067 --> 06:23.534
But please be very careful
with our luggage.

06:23.534 --> 06:24.834
We just got it.

06:24.834 --> 06:26.834
We'll treat it as
if it were our own.

06:26.834 --> 06:29.400
Then I can't let you have it.

06:29.400 --> 06:31.701
Hey, she brought
the camera.

06:31.701 --> 06:33.567
Oh, now,
Steve loves this camera.

06:33.567 --> 06:35.634
Please be very careful
with it.

06:35.634 --> 06:36.701
[DOORBELL RINGS]

06:40.200 --> 06:41.767
Hi, guys.

06:41.767 --> 06:44.601
I was just cleaning out the
garage and I found our luggage.

06:44.601 --> 06:49.167
It's not the greatest,
but it's all we've got.

06:49.167 --> 06:50.767
Someday we'll get good luggage,
but right now,

06:50.767 --> 06:51.834
it will have to do.

06:51.834 --> 06:54.167
And you're more
than welcome to it.

06:54.167 --> 06:58.734
Now, here's our camera.

06:58.734 --> 07:01.234
It's not much,
but it's all we've got.

07:01.234 --> 07:05.167
You're more than welcome to--

07:05.167 --> 07:07.667
Marcie, that's
our good luggage.

07:07.667 --> 07:09.534
You gave them
our good luggage?

07:09.534 --> 07:11.033
Smile!

07:11.033 --> 07:12.834
God, I hate them.

07:12.834 --> 07:16.000
So, where are
you headed?

07:16.000 --> 07:18.067
Well, where's
the one place you would go

07:18.067 --> 07:19.801
if you could go anywhere?

07:19.801 --> 07:20.934
Greece?

07:20.934 --> 07:24.701
That's right, we're going
to Dumpwater, Florida.

07:24.701 --> 07:26.100
U.S. of A.

07:26.100 --> 07:30.367
Dad, our clothes are all
ready for Stinkwater.

07:30.367 --> 07:32.434
That's Dumpwater, kids.

07:32.434 --> 07:36.067
Come here.
Peg, you, too.

07:36.067 --> 07:39.367
Now, I know this is not your
first choice for a vacation.

07:39.367 --> 07:41.334
Does it show, Dad?
Shut up, Bud.

07:41.334 --> 07:44.834
I'm trying to explain something
important to all of you.

07:44.834 --> 07:48.100
Now, we're poor, so we're going
to Dumpwater, Florida.

07:48.100 --> 07:49.901
But let's look
at the positive side.

07:49.901 --> 07:52.267
It's a week where you
don't have to go to school.

07:52.267 --> 07:54.601
It's a week where I don't
have to go to work.

07:54.601 --> 07:56.400
And Peg...

07:56.400 --> 07:57.801
well, every day's
a vacation to you,

07:57.801 --> 07:59.501
so what am I talking
to you for?

07:59.501 --> 08:01.734
Now let's see some smiles,

08:01.734 --> 08:06.400
because tomorrow,
the memories begin.

08:08.234 --> 08:10.801
[CAR ENGINE RUNNING]

